moves.name: Absorb
moves.battle_effect: A GRASS-type attack. It adds half the HP it drained from the target to the attacker's HP.

moves.name: Acid
moves.battle_effect: A POISON-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of lowering the target's DEFENSE.

moves.name: Acid Armor
moves.battle_effect: Melts the user's body for protection. A move that sharply raises DEFENSE.

moves.name: Aeroblast
moves.battle_effect: A powerful FLYING-type attack. It often becomes a critical hit.

moves.name: Agility
moves.battle_effect: A special move that greatly boosts the user's SPEED. Normally used up to three times.

moves.name: Amnesia
moves.battle_effect: A move that increases the user's SPCL.DEF stat. It is normally used up to three times.

moves.name: AncientPower
moves.battle_effect: A ROCK-type attack. This prehistoric move may boost all of the user's stats.

moves.name: Attract
moves.battle_effect: Infatuates targets, making it hard for them to attack foes of the opposite gender.

moves.name: Aurora Beam
moves.battle_effect: An ICE-type attack. Has a  one-in-ten chance of reducing the target's ATTACK power.

moves.name: Barrage
moves.battle_effect: Several spheres are thrown consecutively at the target to inflict damage.

moves.name: Barrier
moves.battle_effect: Instantly forms a barrier between the user and the opponent. DEFENSE is increased.

moves.name: Baton Pass
moves.battle_effect: A move that transfers the user's status changes to the next Pokémon when switching.

moves.name: Beat Up
moves.battle_effect: A DARK-type attack. The user's fellow party Pokémon appear to pummel the target.

moves.name: Belly Drum
moves.battle_effect: A move that allows the user to consume half of its own HP in order to maximize its ATTACK.

moves.name: Bide
moves.battle_effect: The user waits for several turns. At the end, it returns double the damage it received.

moves.name: Bind
moves.battle_effect: Traps and squeezes the target over several turns. The target cannot move while under attack.

moves.name: Bite
moves.battle_effect: A bite made using sharp fangs. This may cause the opponent to flinch, and it might not attack.

moves.name: Blizzard
moves.battle_effect: The strongest ICE-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of freezing the target.

moves.name: Body Slam
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of paralyzing the target if it hits.

moves.name: Bone Club
moves.battle_effect: A physical attack using a bone as a club. If it connects, it may cause the target to flinch.

moves.name: Bonemerang
moves.battle_effect: A boomerang made of bone is thrown to inflict damage twice, on the way out and on return.

moves.name: Bone Rush
moves.battle_effect: A GROUND-type attack. The attacker uses a bone to club the foe two to five times.

moves.name: Bubble
moves.battle_effect: A WATER-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of reducing the target's SPEED.

moves.name: BubbleBeam
moves.battle_effect: A WATER-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of reducing the target's SPEED.

moves.name: Charm
moves.battle_effect: A move that charms the target into complacency, sharply reducing its ATTACK power.

moves.name: Clamp
moves.battle_effect: Grips the target in the attacker's shell for two to five turns.

moves.name: Comet Punch
moves.battle_effect: Although each slap is weak, this attack hits the target two to five times in succession.

moves.name: Confuse Ray
moves.battle_effect: A sinister flash of light makes the target confused. A special GHOST-type move.

moves.name: Confusion
moves.battle_effect: A PSYCHIC-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of leaving the target confused.

moves.name: Constrict
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of reducing the target's SPEED.

moves.name: Conversion
moves.battle_effect: A special move that switches the user's elemental type into  one of the user's attack types.

moves.name: Conversion 2
moves.battle_effect: A move that changes the user's type into one that is resistant to the opponent's last move.

moves.name: Cotton Spore
moves.battle_effect: Spores that cling to the target, sharply reducing the opponent's SPEED.

moves.name: Counter
moves.battle_effect: A retaliation move that pays back double the damage of a physical attack. Very accurate.

moves.name: Crabhammer
moves.battle_effect: A move that is used only by Pokémon with pincers. Likely to get a critical hit.

moves.name: Cross Chop
moves.battle_effect: A FIGHTING-type attack. It is powerful and often lands a critical hit.

moves.name: Crunch
moves.battle_effect: A DARK-type attack. Has a one-in-five chance of reducing the target's SPCL.DEF.

moves.name: Curse
moves.battle_effect: Raises ATTACK and DEFENSE at the expense of SPEED. It works differently for the GHOST type.

moves.name: Cut
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. Also used for cutting small bushes to open new paths.

moves.name: Defense Curl
moves.battle_effect: Raises the user's DEFENSE. Can normally be used up to six times in a row.

moves.name: Destiny Bond
moves.battle_effect: A move that causes the opponent to faint if the user faints after using this move.

moves.name: Detect
moves.battle_effect: Allows user to completely evade attack. If used consecutively, its success rate decreases.

moves.name: Dig
moves.battle_effect: The attacker digs underground in the first turn, then pops up in the next turn to attack.

moves.name: Disable
moves.battle_effect: A move that disables one of the target's moves. That move can't be used until it wears off.

moves.name: Dizzy Punch
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. Has a  one-in-five chance of leaving the target confused.

moves.name: Double-Edge
moves.battle_effect: A charging tackle attack. One quarter of the damage comes back to hurt the attacker.

moves.name: Double Kick
moves.battle_effect: A FIGHTING-type attack. As the name implies, it is actually two quick kicks in succession.

moves.name: DoubleSlap
moves.battle_effect: Although each slap is weak, this attack hits the target two to five times in succession.

moves.name: Double Team
moves.battle_effect: Creates illusionary copies of the user. They disorient the enemy, reducing its accuracy.

moves.name: DragonBreath
moves.battle_effect: A DRAGON-type attack. Has a  one-in-three chance of paralyzing the target.

moves.name: Dragon Rage
moves.battle_effect: A DRAGON-type attack. It always inflicts a set amount of damage.

moves.name: Dream Eater
moves.battle_effect: Works only on sleeping Pokémon. Steals the target's HP and adds 50%% of it to the user's HP.

moves.name: Drill Peck
moves.battle_effect: A standard FLYING-type attack. It is strong and highly likely to hit the target.

moves.name: DynamicPunch
moves.battle_effect: A FIGHTING-type attack. Inaccurate but guaranteed to confuse the opponent if it hits.

moves.name: Earthquake
moves.battle_effect: An attack that inflicts damage by shaking the ground. Useless against the FLYING type.

moves.name: Egg Bomb
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. An egg is launched at the target. It may miss, however.

moves.name: Ember
moves.battle_effect: A FIRE-type attack. Has a onein-ten chance of leaving the target with a damaging burn.

moves.name: Encore
moves.battle_effect: Forces the target to continue to use the move it used last for the next two to six turns.

moves.name: Endure
moves.battle_effect: Always leaves the user with at least one HP. Success rate decreases if used repeatedly.

moves.name: Explosion
moves.battle_effect: The most powerful attack of all. However, the attacker faints after using this move.

moves.name: ExtremeSpeed
moves.battle_effect: An attack that always strikes first. It can be learned by only a few Pokémon.

moves.name: Faint Attack
moves.battle_effect: A DARK-type attack. The move catches the opponent off guard, so it never misses.

moves.name: False Swipe
moves.battle_effect: A move that adjusts ATTACK so that the foe has one HP left.  Can't cause the foe to faint.

moves.name: Fire Blast
moves.battle_effect: Strongest FIRE-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of inflicting a burn on the target.

moves.name: Fire Punch
moves.battle_effect: A special FIRE-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of inflicting a burn on the target.

moves.name: Fire Spin
moves.battle_effect: A FIRE-type attack that lasts two to five turns. The flames make the target unable to move.

moves.name: Fissure
moves.battle_effect: Causes a single-hit knockout if it hits. Useless against FLYING-type Pokémon.

moves.name: Flail
moves.battle_effect: An attack that increases in power if the user's HP is low. It could turn the tide in battle.

moves.name: Flamethrower
moves.battle_effect: A powerful FIRE-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of leaving the target with a burn.

moves.name: Flame Wheel
moves.battle_effect: A FIRE-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of inflicting a burn on the target.

moves.name: Flash
moves.battle_effect: Blinds the target with a bright flash of light, reducing the  opponent's accuracy.

moves.name: Fly
moves.battle_effect: The Pokémon flies high, then strikes in the next turn. Used to fly to places already visited.

moves.name: Focus Energy
moves.battle_effect: Raises the likelihood of nailing the opponent's weak spot for a critical hit.

moves.name: Foresight
moves.battle_effect: Neutralizes the foe's evasiveness. Also makes the GHOST type vulnerable to physical attacks.

moves.name: Frustration
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. The more the user dislikes its trainer, the more powerful the move.

moves.name: Fury Attack
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. The Pokémon rapidly jabs at its opponent several times.

moves.name: Fury Cutter
moves.battle_effect: A BUG-type attack that grows more powerful with every hit. Returns to normal if it misses.

moves.name: Fury Swipes
moves.battle_effect: The target is scratched by sharp claws two to five times in quick succession.

moves.name: Future Sight
moves.battle_effect: A special PSYCHIC-type attack. It strikes the target two turns after it is used.

moves.name: Giga Drain
moves.battle_effect: Half of the HP drained from the target is added to the attacker's HP.

moves.name: Glare
moves.battle_effect: Transfixes the enemy with terrifying sharp eyes,  frightening it into paralysis.

moves.name: Growl
moves.battle_effect: A move that lowers the target's ATTACK power. Can normally be used up to six times.

moves.name: Growth
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type move that raises SPCL.ATK. Normally used up to six times.

moves.name: Guillotine
moves.battle_effect: A single-hit knockout attack. Learned only by Pokémon that have large pincers.

moves.name: Gust
moves.battle_effect: A FLYING-type attack. The bird Pokémon flaps its wings to create a powerful wind.

moves.name: Harden
moves.battle_effect: Raises the user's DEFENSE. Useful when battling physically strong Pokémon.

moves.name: Haze
moves.battle_effect: Eliminates all changes affecting stats, such as SPEED, of both Pokémon in battle.

moves.name: Headbutt
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of making the target flinch if it hits.

moves.name: Heal Bell
moves.battle_effect: The soothing ringing of a bell that eliminates all status problems for the entire party.

moves.name: Hidden Power
moves.battle_effect: A peculiar move that changes type and power depending on the Pokémon using it.

moves.name: Hi Jump Kick
moves.battle_effect: Stronger than JUMP KICK. If it misses, the attacker takes 1/8 the damage it would've caused.

moves.name: Horn Attack
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. A sharp horn is driven hard into the target to inflict damage.

moves.name: Horn Drill
moves.battle_effect: A single-hit knockout attack. Learned only by Pokémon with a horn or horns.

moves.name: Hydro Pump
moves.battle_effect: The strongest WATER-type attack. While it is powerful, it may miss the target.

moves.name: Hyper Beam
moves.battle_effect: An extremely powerful attack. The attacker becomes so tired, it has to rest the next turn.

moves.name: Hyper Fang
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of making the target flinch.

moves.name: Hypnosis
moves.battle_effect: A special PSYCHIC-type move. The target is hypnotized into a deep sleep.

moves.name: Ice Beam
moves.battle_effect: An ICE-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of freezing the target solid.

moves.name: Ice Punch
moves.battle_effect: A special ICE-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of freezing the target.

moves.name: Icy Wind
moves.battle_effect: An ICE-type attack. It is guaranteed to reduce the target's SPEED if it hits.

moves.name: Iron Tail
moves.battle_effect: Strikes the target with a stiff tail. Has a one-in-three shot at lowering the target's DEFENSE.

moves.name: Jump Kick
moves.battle_effect: A forceful FIGHTING-type attack. If it misses, however, the attacker gets hurt.

moves.name: Karate Chop
moves.battle_effect: A FIGHTING-type attack. Often turns into a critical hit and inflicts double the damage.

moves.name: Kinesis
moves.battle_effect: A special move of bending spoons to confound the enemy. Makes the user harder to hit.

moves.name: Leech Life
moves.battle_effect: An HP-draining attack. It adds half the HP it drained from  the target to the attacker's HP.

moves.name: Leech Seed
moves.battle_effect: Plants a seed on the target Pokémon. It slowly drains the target's HP for the attacker.

moves.name: Leer
moves.battle_effect: A move that lowers the target's DEFENSE. Useful against tough, armored Pokémon.

moves.name: Lick
moves.battle_effect: A GHOST-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of leaving the target with paralysis.

moves.name: Light Screen
moves.battle_effect: Reduces damage from special attacks by about half. A special PSYCHIC-type move.

moves.name: Lock-On
moves.battle_effect: An attack that locks on to the target to ensure that the next attack will hit without fail.

moves.name: Lovely Kiss
moves.battle_effect: A special move that puts the target to sleep with a big kiss. (Actually, the victim faints.)

moves.name: Low Kick
moves.battle_effect: A FIGHTING-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of making the target flinch if it hits.

moves.name: Mach Punch
moves.battle_effect: An incredibly fast punch that always lands first.

moves.name: Magnitude
moves.battle_effect: A GROUND-type attack. The power of the attack will vary each time it is used.

moves.name: Mean Look
moves.battle_effect: A probing stare that prevents the target from escaping until the attacking Pokémon is gone.

moves.name: Meditate
moves.battle_effect: A special move that boosts the user's ATTACK power. Can normally be used up to six times.

moves.name: Mega Drain
moves.battle_effect: A GRASS-type attack. It adds half the HP it drained from the target to the attacker's HP.

moves.name: Megahorn
moves.battle_effect: A BUG-type attack that uses a stiff horn or horns. It is rarely learned.

moves.name: Mega Kick
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. Out of all the Pokémon kicking attacks, this is the strongest.

moves.name: Mega Punch
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack move. It is highly accurate and relatively powerful.

moves.name: Metal Claw
moves.battle_effect: Strikes the target with sharp claws. Has a one-in-ten shot at raising the user's ATTACK.

moves.name: Metronome
moves.battle_effect: The user waggles its finger, triggering a move. There is no telling what will happen.

moves.name: Milk Drink
moves.battle_effect: A move that restores HP by half of the user's max HP. This move may also be used in the field.

moves.name: Mimic
moves.battle_effect: A move for learning one of the opponent's moves, for use during that battle only.

moves.name: Mind Reader
moves.battle_effect: It predicts the opponent's movement. The user's next attack will never miss.

moves.name: Minimize
moves.battle_effect: Reduces the user's size and makes it harder to hit. Can normally be used up to six times.

moves.name: Mirror Coat
moves.battle_effect: The foe will receive double the damage the user sustained from a special attack. High accuracy.

moves.name: Mirror Move
moves.battle_effect: A move that strikes back with the opponent's last move. It comes after the enemy's move.

moves.name: Mist
moves.battle_effect: Provides full protection against any enemy status attack.

moves.name: Moonlight
moves.battle_effect: Allows HP to be restored by the moonlight. In battle, half the user's max HP is restored.

moves.name: Morning Sun
moves.battle_effect: Allows HP to be restored by the morning sunlight. In battle, half the user's max HP is restored.

moves.name: Mud-Slap
moves.battle_effect: An attack that fires dirt, inflicting damage and reducing the target's accuracy.

moves.name: Nightmare
moves.battle_effect: A move that makes a sleeping target have bad dreams. The victim will steadily lose HP.

moves.name: Night Shade
moves.battle_effect: A GHOST-type attack. Highly accurate, it always inflicts damage.

moves.name: Octazooka
moves.battle_effect: An attack that shoots ink. Has a fifty-fifty chance of reducing the target's accuracy.

moves.name: Outrage
moves.battle_effect: An attack that lasts two to three turns. Afterwards, the attacker will become confused.

moves.name: Pain Split
moves.battle_effect: A move that adds the HPs of the user and the target, then divides the total between them.

moves.name: Pay Day
moves.battle_effect: A move that nets money at the end of battle. How much depends on attack frequency and level.

moves.name: Peck
moves.battle_effect: A standard FLYING-type attack. It is favored by Pokémon with beaks or horns.

moves.name: Perish Song
moves.battle_effect: A malevolent melody that causes both the user and the opponent to faint in three turns.

moves.name: Petal Dance
moves.battle_effect: A dance-like attack that lasts two to three turns. The attacker becomes confused.

moves.name: Pin Missile
moves.battle_effect: An attack that fires many  needle-like projectiles from the body. Strikes several times.

moves.name: Poison Gas
moves.battle_effect: A poisonous cloud of gas is forcefully expelled to poison the target.

moves.name: PoisonPowder
moves.battle_effect: A move that poisons the target. If poisoned, the victim loses HP steadily.

moves.name: Poison Sting
moves.battle_effect: A POISON-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of leaving the target poisoned.

moves.name: Pound
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. Slightly stronger than TACKLE. Many Pokémon know this move.

moves.name: Powder Snow
moves.battle_effect: An ICE-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of freezing the target.

moves.name: Present
moves.battle_effect: A move that inflicts major damage but may restore the target's HP.

moves.name: Protect
moves.battle_effect: Completely foils an opponent's attack. If used consecutively, its success rate decreases.

moves.name: Psybeam
moves.battle_effect: A PSYCHIC-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of making the target confused.

moves.name: Psychic
moves.battle_effect: A PSYCHIC-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of lowering the target's SPCL.DEF rating.

moves.name: Psych Up
moves.battle_effect: Self-hypnosis move that copies the foe's stats changes, then applies them to the user.

moves.name: Psywave
moves.battle_effect: A PSYCHIC-type attack of varying intensity. It occasionally inflicts heavy damage.

moves.name: Pursuit
moves.battle_effect: A DARK-type attack. It inflicts major damage if the target switches out in the same turn.

moves.name: Quick Attack
moves.battle_effect: Always strikes first. If both Pokémon use this, the one with higher SPEED attacks first.

moves.name: Rage
moves.battle_effect: A non-stop attack move. The user's ATTACK power increases every time it sustains damage.

moves.name: Rain Dance
moves.battle_effect: Summons rain for five turns. While it is raining, the power of WATER-type moves increases.

moves.name: Rapid Spin
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. By spinning quickly, the user can escape from restraining moves.

moves.name: Razor Leaf
moves.battle_effect: A GRASS-type attack that uses sharp-edged leaves. Likely to get a critical hit.

moves.name: Razor Wind
moves.battle_effect: A two-turn attack with the wind attack in the second turn. Learned by many FLYING types.

moves.name: Recover
moves.battle_effect: Half of the user's maximum HP is restored. Few Pokémon learn this move on their own.

moves.name: Reflect
moves.battle_effect: Reduces damage from physical attacks by about half. A special PSYCHIC-type move.

moves.name: Rest
moves.battle_effect: The user takes a nap to fully restore its HP and recover from any status abnormalities.

moves.name: Return
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. The tamer the user, the more powerful the move.

moves.name: Reversal
moves.battle_effect: An attack that increases in power if the user's HP is low. It could turn the tide in battle.

moves.name: Roar
moves.battle_effect: A terrifying roar that drives the target away. The opposing  trainer must use a new Pokémon.

moves.name: Rock Slide
moves.battle_effect: A ROCK-type attack that hits the target with an avalanche of rocks and boulders.

moves.name: Rock Smash
moves.battle_effect: A FIGHTING-type attack. In the field, it can be used to shatter rocks to open new paths.

moves.name: Rock Throw
moves.battle_effect: A ROCK-type attack. As the name implies, a huge boulder is dropped on the target.

moves.name: Rolling Kick
moves.battle_effect: A sharp FIGHTING-type attack. Has a one-in-three shot at making the target flinch.

moves.name: Rollout
moves.battle_effect: Attacks for five turns, growing more powerful each time. Power returns to normal if it misses.

moves.name: Sacred Fire
moves.battle_effect: A FIRE-type attack. Has a onein-two chance of leaving the target with a burn.

moves.name: Safeguard
moves.battle_effect: A mystic power that protects the user from status problems for five turns.

moves.name: Sand-Attack
moves.battle_effect: An attack in which sand is used to blind the target and reduce its attack accuracy.

moves.name: Sandstorm
moves.battle_effect: An attack that creates a sandstorm. The effect causes damage to both combatants.

moves.name: Scary Face
moves.battle_effect: A horrific look that scares the victim, sharply reducing the target's SPEED.

moves.name: Scratch
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. Sharp claws are used to inflict damage on the target.

moves.name: Screech
moves.battle_effect: A move that makes a horrible noise. It sharply reduces the target's DEFENSE.

moves.name: Seismic Toss
moves.battle_effect: A FIGHTING-type attack. Throws the target with enough force to flip the world.

moves.name: Selfdestruct
moves.battle_effect: The user explodes, damaging the enemy, then faints. Useless against the GHOST type.

moves.name: Shadow Ball
moves.battle_effect: A GHOST-type attack. Has a  one-in-five chance of reducing the target's SPCL.DEF.

moves.name: Sharpen
moves.battle_effect: Raises the user's ATTACK power. The edges of the Pokémon are made harder for more impact.

moves.name: Sing
moves.battle_effect: A special NORMAL-type move. A soothing melody lulls the target to sleep.

moves.name: Sketch
moves.battle_effect: A move that allows the user to copy a move used by an opponent and learn that move.

moves.name: Skull Bash
moves.battle_effect: In the first turn, the attacker tucks its head. The next turn, it head-butts at full steam.

moves.name: Sky Attack
moves.battle_effect: Strongest FLYING-type attack. Stores energy in the first turn, then fires in the next.

moves.name: Slam
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack move. The attacker uses an appendage to slam the target hard.

moves.name: Slash
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. It has a high probability of a critical hit for inflicting double damage.

moves.name: Sleep Powder
moves.battle_effect: Induces sleep. A Pokémon will stay asleep for several turns if an item isn't used to wake it.

moves.name: Sleep Talk
moves.battle_effect: Randomly chooses one of the user's moves. Can be used only by a sleeping Pokémon.

moves.name: Sludge
moves.battle_effect: A POISON-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of poisoning the target.

moves.name: Sludge Bomb
moves.battle_effect: A POISON-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of leaving the target poisoned.

moves.name: Smog
moves.battle_effect: Smog is spewed as a cloud. Has a fifty-fifty chance of poisoning the target.

moves.name: SmokeScreen
moves.battle_effect: Creates an obscuring cloud of smoke that reduces the enemy's accuracy.

moves.name: Snore
moves.battle_effect: Has a one-in-three chance of making the target flinch. Can be used only by a sleeping Pokémon.

moves.name: Softboiled
moves.battle_effect: Half of the user's maximum HP is restored. May also be used in the field.

moves.name: SolarBeam
moves.battle_effect: Strongest GRASS-type attack. Energy is absorbed in the first turn, then fired on the next.

moves.name: SonicBoom
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. It always inflicts a set amount of damage.

moves.name: Spark
moves.battle_effect: An ELECTRIC-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of paralyzing the target.

moves.name: Spider Web
moves.battle_effect: Sticky strings that prevent the target from escaping until the attacking Pokémon is gone.

moves.name: Spike Cannon
moves.battle_effect: A physical attack consisting of two to five consecutive hits. Highly accurate.

moves.name: Spikes
moves.battle_effect: An attack that scatters SPIKES and injures opponent Pokémon when they switch.

moves.name: Spite
moves.battle_effect: A vengeful move that slightly reduces the PP of the opponent's last move.

moves.name: Splash
moves.battle_effect: A move that involves only flopping and SPLASHing around. It has no effect.

moves.name: Spore
moves.battle_effect: Special spores are scattered from mushrooms. If the foe inhales them, it will fall asleep.

moves.name: Steel Wing
moves.battle_effect: Strikes the target with stiff wings. Has a one-in-ten chance of raising the user's DEFENSE.

moves.name: Stomp
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. Has a one-in-three chance of making the target flinch if it hits.

moves.name: Strength
moves.battle_effect: A very powerful NORMAL-type attack. Also used for moving obstacles like boulders.

moves.name: String Shot
moves.battle_effect: Strings are sprayed out and wrapped around the target to reduce its SPEED.

moves.name: Stun Spore
moves.battle_effect: Special move that causes paralysis. The victim has a one-infour chance of immobility.

moves.name: Submission
moves.battle_effect: Strongest FIGHTING attack. One quarter of the damage also hurts the attacker.

moves.name: Substitute
moves.battle_effect: Uses 1/4 of the user's maximum HP to create a substitute that takes the opponent's attacks.

moves.name: Sunny Day
moves.battle_effect: Makes the weather sunny for five turns. When sunny, FIRE-type moves are more powerful.

moves.name: Super Fang
moves.battle_effect: If it hits, this attack cuts the target's HP in half. Learned by Pokémon with developed fangs.

moves.name: Supersonic
moves.battle_effect: A special NORMAL-type move. Supersonic sound waves are used to confuse the target.

moves.name: Surf
moves.battle_effect: A WATER-type attack. This move is strong and highly accurate.

moves.name: Swagger
moves.battle_effect: A move that infuriates and  confuses the opponent, but it increases the target's ATTACK.

moves.name: Sweet Kiss
moves.battle_effect: A sweet little kiss that causes the target to become giddy and confused.

moves.name: Sweet Scent
moves.battle_effect: A pleasant aroma that distracts the target, making the opponent easier to hit.

moves.name: Swift
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. It is highly accurate, so it can be counted on to inflict damage.

moves.name: Swords Dance
moves.battle_effect: A special move that boosts the user's ATTACK power. Normally used up to three times.

moves.name: Synthesis
moves.battle_effect: Allows HP to be restored by the sunlight. In battle, half the user's max HP is restored.

moves.name: Tackle
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. Many Pokémon know this attack right from the start.

moves.name: Tail Whip
moves.battle_effect: A move that lowers the target's DEFENSE. Useful against tough, armored Pokémon.

moves.name: Take Down
moves.battle_effect: A charging attack. One quarter of the damage it inflicts comes back to hurt the attacker.

moves.name: Teleport
moves.battle_effect: A special move for instantly escaping from wild Pokémon. Useful in the wild only.

moves.name: Thief
moves.battle_effect: A DARK-type attack. The attacking Pokémon may steal an item held by the target.

moves.name: Thrash
moves.battle_effect: An attack that lasts two to three turns. Afterwards, the attacker becomes confused.

moves.name: Thunder
moves.battle_effect: Strongest of all ELECTRIC-type attacks. Has a one-in-ten shot at paralyzing the target.

moves.name: Thunderbolt
moves.battle_effect: An ELECTRIC-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of paralyzing the target.

moves.name: ThunderPunch
moves.battle_effect: A special ELECTRIC-type attack. Has a one-in-ten shot at paralyzing the target.

moves.name: ThunderShock
moves.battle_effect: An ELECTRIC-type attack. Has a one-in-ten chance of paralyzing the target.

moves.name: Thunder Wave
moves.battle_effect: A special move that causes paralysis. The victim has a onein-four chance of immobility.

moves.name: Toxic
moves.battle_effect: A move that badly poisons the target. The amount of poison damage increases every turn.

moves.name: Transform
moves.battle_effect: Transforms user into a copy of the target, including the type. All moves have only five PP each.

moves.name: Tri Attack
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack. A triangular field of energy is created and launched.

moves.name: Triple Kick
moves.battle_effect: A three-kick attack that inflicts increasing damage. When one kick misses, the move ends.

moves.name: Twineedle
moves.battle_effect: An attack that strikes twice. The target may occasionally become poisoned.

moves.name: Twister
moves.battle_effect: A DRAGON-type attack. Has a  one-in-five chance of causing the target to flinch.

moves.name: ViceGrip
moves.battle_effect: A NORMAL-type attack used only by Pokémon with pincers. The target is gripped and injured.

moves.name: Vine Whip
moves.battle_effect: A GRASS-type attack. The Pokémon uses its cruel whips to strike the opponent.

moves.name: Vital Throw
moves.battle_effect: A FIGHTING-type attack. Always comes after the target's attack but never misses.

moves.name: Waterfall
moves.battle_effect: A WATER-type attack. Hits with a blow packing the power of fish traveling up waterfalls.

moves.name: Water Gun
moves.battle_effect: A WATER-type attack. Stronger than BUBBLE. Many WATER-type Pokémon learn this move.

moves.name: Whirlpool
moves.battle_effect: Lasts two to five turns. Foe becomes trapped in a vortex, making it impossible to switch.

moves.name: Whirlwind
moves.battle_effect: A powerful wind that blows the target away. The opposing trainer must use a new Pokémon.

moves.name: Wing Attack
moves.battle_effect: A FLYING-type attack. The attacking  Pokémon spreads its wings and charges.

moves.name: Withdraw
moves.battle_effect: Used mainly by Pokémon with shells. By withdrawing into the shell, DEFENSE is increased.

moves.name: Wrap
moves.battle_effect: Traps and squeezes the target over two to five turns, making the target unable to move.

moves.name: Zap Cannon
moves.battle_effect: An ELECTRIC-type attack. Inaccurate but is guaranteed to cause paralysis if it hits.
